# Companion .dockerignore for cowork/Dockerfile.
#
# BuildKit applies <dockerfile-path>.dockerignore as a companion file when
# present, taking priority over a context-root .dockerignore. Naming this
# file Dockerfile.dockerignore (matching the sibling Dockerfile) means the
# rules below apply regardless of where the build context root sits — the
# cowork/ directory itself (git-mode build) or a parent like antonworld/
# / mindsdb/ that also contains anton/ (local-mode build).
#
# Patterns use **/ globs because the cowork tree may sit at the context
# root (git mode) or under cowork/ (local mode), and the anton/ sibling
# (local mode) needs the same hygiene applied to its subtree.

# Build artifacts — produced inside the image.
**/node_modules/
**/dist/
**/out/
**/release/
**/build/

# Editor / OS / agent junk.
**/.DS_Store
**/Thumbs.db
**/.vscode/
**/.idea/
**/.cursor/
**/.claude/
**/*.swp

# Source-control internals — not needed for builds, and shipping .git to
# a customer leaks commit history. Critical for security review.
**/.git/
**/.gitignore
**/.gitattributes
**/.github/

# Environment / secrets — never bake into images. The negation keeps the
# .env.example template available so docs/setup scripts can read it.
**/.env
**/.env.*
!**/.env.example
**/*.pem
**/*.key
**/*.p12
**/*.pfx

# Python caches and local virtualenvs. The local anton/.venv on the host
# is a macOS-built venv with darwin .so files — useless on Linux and a
# source of phantom CVE findings if it slips into the image.
**/__pycache__/
**/*.pyc
**/*.pyo
**/.pytest_cache/
**/.mypy_cache/
**/.ruff_cache/
**/.venv/
**/venv/
**/.pytest-workspace/
**/scratchpad-venvs/
**/htmlcov/
**/.coverage
**/.coverage.*

# Anton runtime state directory (vault, conversations, settings) — host
# data that must not be baked in.
**/.anton/

# Logs.
**/*.log
**/logs/

# Documentation drafts and the throwaway port-audit.
**/docs/web-port-audit.md
